  "instructions": [
    "Heat the sesame oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the ginger and garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the pork shoulder and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the beetroot, brown sugar, soy sauce, crushed red pepper, and rice vinegar.",
    "Stir to combine, then add the water and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.",
    "Stir in the honey and cook for an additional 2 minutes.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with green onions.",
    "Serve over rice or noodles, if desired.",
    "Let the tagine rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Carve the pork into thin slices and serve with the beetroot and sauce.",
    "Enjoy!"
